<p><?php echo __('Use the shortcode <code>[bzkshopping]</code> in the body of an article, page or widget to display products automatically based on context.', 'bazooka-shopping') ?></p><p><?php echo __('The attribute <code>keyword</code> allows you to manually force the product query. Example: <code>[bzkshopping keyword="drill"]</code> will display drills.', 'bazooka-shopping') ?></p><p><?php echo __('The attribute <code>count</code> allows to specify the number of products. Example: <code>[bzkshopping count="3"]</code> will display 3 products.', 'bazooka-shopping') ?></p><p><?php echo __('The attribute <code>template</code> allows to specify the design of the list. Example: <code>[bzkshopping template="box"]</code> will display products in box mode.', 'bazooka-shopping') ?><br> <?php echo sprintf(__('Possible values are : %s.', 'bazooka-shopping'), '<code>'.implode('</code>, <code>', array_keys(Bazooka_Shopping::$templates)).'</code>') ?></p><p><?php echo __('The attribute <code>merchants</code> allows to choose which merchants to display, and the order in which they are displayed. Example: <code>[bzkshopping merchants="ebay,amazon"]</code> will display products from eBay and Amazon only.', 'bazooka-shopping') ?><br> <?php echo sprintf(__('Possible values are : %s.', 'bazooka-shopping'), '<code>'.implode('</code>, <code>', array_keys(Bazooka_Shopping::$merchants)).'</code>') ?></p><p><?php echo __('These attributes are cumulative. Example: <code>[bzkshopping keyword="vacuum cleaner" count="8" template="grid" merchants="amazon"]</code> will display a grid of 8 vacuum cleaners from Amazon.', 'bazooka-shopping') ?></p>